modules.description: Generates OCaml code from Swagger 2.0 API definitions, producing client libraries with typed request and response handlers. It processes OpenAPI specifications, extracting endpoints, parameters, and data models to create modular, type-safe bindings. Used to build the Kubernetes API client in Kubecaml, ensuring compatibility with complex, real-world API structures.

Generates code from OpenAPI specifications using provided base paths and reference configurations. It processes input JSON or YAML files and writes output to a specified channel or standard output. The module supports structured API definitions and reference hierarchies for code generation workflows.
